g.title: cluster0
g.text: Sync for each device (lastReq and local dayModified flags specific to device)

g.title: cluster3
g.text: Old device computer uploads data out of order (device was moved)

g.title: computerSyncsAllRemoteDeviceOneData
g.text: Computer fully syncs data from remote device 1

g.title: deviceTwoUploadsAfterBeingOfflineForADay
g.text: Remote device 2 uploads after losing internet for 2 days (or minutes)

g.title: computerNeverAsksForDeviceTwosDataFromYesterday
g.text: Computer never asks for device 2 data older than latest device 1 data

g.title: comment1
g.text: There is a version of this problem where data is lost.

g.title: comment2
g.text: However we can avoid it by fully syncing and signing out PCs before moving devices.
